title.44: Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Annual (1979) #4

description.1: Kitty Pryde's father is in hot water with some Japanese businessmen. Things get worse when she stows away on a flight to Tokyo.
description.5: Daredevil must choose sides! Is he with... the Kingpin of Crime? Or is he with... Micah Synn, a barbarian with a heart of pure ice? Talk about no-win situations!
description.6: Exiled to the Crossroads Dimension, the Hulk comes across the Puffball Collective. Doctor Strange is a close onlooker.
description.7: Tony Stark is holed up in his lab, working on a project that has the new Iron Man, James Rhodes, more than a little worried! Does it mean Rhodey will have to give up the armor? Meanwhile, the Brothers Grimm are gunning for his metallic hide, and that's no fairy tale!
description.9: The team time travels to the Ol' American Frontier in search of Reed's lost father. The FF is not only shocked by the technology the frontiersmen have...but who their mysterious leader is!
description.10: Storm, Naze, and Forge are attacked by Dire Wraiths. Can a powerless Storm fight off these alien invaders?
description.11: In the ravages of a New York snowstorm, Dagger is missing. Spider-Man and Black Cat join forces to find the super heroine, but will their pursuit prove fruitless? Mary Jane contemplates her place in Spider-Man's life, while Kingpin makes his next move.
description.12: Wonder Man, Tigra and Shroud duke it out alone against Graviton, with their pride, and possibly the Avengers' future, at stake!
description.15: Luke finds himself fighting more for revenge than for freedom...is he on the path to the dark side?
description.16: After weird dreams and prolonged sleep, Spider-Man decides to visit the Fantastic Four at the Baxter Building! Curious to find out what Spidey's alien suit is made of, Reed Richards conducts an assessment. The findings are both shocking and sinister!
description.17: The Casket of Ancient Winters, an Asgardian power object, has unleashed blizzards everywhere on Earth! Now, the Avengers must band together with rest of Earth's heroes to battle the fire-demon Surtur and his hordes!
description.18: His friends want to find him! His Foes want to kill him! This is Captain America's last stand!
description.20: Conan returns to the mysterious island of the giants and soon discovers that the legendary giants have returned to reclaim what is rightfully theirs!
description.23: Read letters from Marvel Super Heroes in this special edition of Marvel Age.
description.25: Ben's feelings for Alicia become more confused when he shares a passionate kiss with Tarianna! Later, Ben falls victim to a village of other subterranean Thing-like creatures!
description.27: When smalltime crook Erik Josten gets a dose of Pym particles he becomes the mega man Goliath! Iron Man has his hands full and his repulsors charged, trying to wipe out Goliath before Goliath wipes out Los Angeles! The West Coast Avengers assemble in this giant-sized battle for the streets!
description.31: Still the greatest sightless super hero in all of comics! Fighting a menace he's never faced before - the likes of which he's likely never to meet again! And that's only the beginning! If you think you've seen ol' hornhead in red-hot action - see this!
description.32: Hulk's blind anger and rage have entirely replaced Banner's humanity. Marvel's finest heroes assemble to take down the Hulk...but their efforts prove futile.
description.33: Meet the latest Marvel super villain! His name is Vibro! His power is that of superhuman vibration, and he's going to shake you up! He's got the power to beat Iron Man, while Tony Stark is taking care of business of his own in Silicon Valley.
description.36: It's a not-so-happy birthday for Reed Richards! Realizing he's lost many precious memories in the Negative Zone, Reed and his team, alongside Wyatt Wingfoot and She-Hulk, head to his family home. Will Reed finally regain his memories?
description.37: Now powerless and depressed, Storm is taken in by the mutant Forge, who tries to alleviate her anguish. Meanwhile, Dr. Valerie Cooper is attacked by Dire Wraiths!
description.38: Silvermane brutally defeats Spider-Man and only the Black Cat can save him. Can the heroes and Cloak and Dagger beat Silvermane and the Rose?
description.39: The West Coast team springs into action as they begin extensive, and exhaustive, training. Wonder Man questions himself as a hero when some small-time crooks get the better of him. Plus, Graviton crashes the scene!
description.42: Dazzler attempts to solve a crime surrounding a teleportation kidnapping of super models!
description.45: Black Cat and Puma claw it out, but the new foe stands undefeated! He prowls onward and pounces on Spider-Man! Meanwhile, the Rose and Kingpin brood over Spider-Man's fate.
description.46: When Maelstrom targets the Uni-Mind in an evil plot to kill the Eternals, The Avengers spring into action to save them. Will the Avengers' combined might be enough to stop Maelstrom and his ally, Deathurge? Find out in this action-packed issue!
description.47: At long last! The Shocking tale of the man behind the mask! The life and times of the Red Skull!
description.48: It's a diplomatic mission, just perfect for Princess Leia and Mon Mothma to handle-until they stumble upon Imperial forces fighting to control a strategic stronghold! And the Imperial forces are winning!
description.51: Alpha Flight rides in to the rescue!
description.52: “Look out, world! Here comes Star Comics!”
description.55: Trapped in a wintry wasteland without food or water, Conan and his band must face starvation— or something far, far worse!
description.61: Ben and Tarianna are enjoying each other's company, when they are interrupted by Gruhl of Shalfbut!
description.63: The Avengers make their West Coast debut! Newlyweds Hawkeye and Mockingbird check out a California compound while awaiting the arrival of their team. Enter the mysterious Shroud! Plus, Tigra and Iron Man join the Cali-crew!
description.66: Micah Synn hits the Kingpin where it hurts the most! That'll give you some idea of his power - and then, he challenges Daredevil to break the laws he's sworn to protect! What can D.D. do with his back against the wall? He doesn't have time to find out - because Crossbow returns! And who do you think he's hunting this time!
description.67: Tony Stark arrives. He's in Silicon Valley, ready to re-build his business from the ground up. It seems like he's got his alcoholism problem licked, but can he cope with seeing Rhodey in his Iron Man uniform? You knew this dramatic confrontation had to come.
description.69: While Reed, She-Hulk and Wyatt battle Terminus in the Wild West, romance blossoms...between Johnny and Alicia!?
description.70: A meeting between Storm and Rogue goes horribly wrong when Rogue is attacked by Gyrich's crew, who are packing some major heat-Forge's neutralizer.
description.71: Silvermane has Spider-Man in his crosshairs and doesn't care that he has a date with the Black Cat to get to! Plus, Cloak and Dagger continue their war on drugs!
description.73: In the magical world beyond the mist, Conan has an uncanny lookalike!
description.75: The first appearance of Puma!  As his new alien costume continues to influence his behavior, Spider-Man goes after the Rose. In retaliation, Rose hires Puma to pounce on our web-slinging hero! Will Spider-Man be able to overcome both his suit…and his new foe?
description.76: In this issue: The Eternals reveal their origin and the truth about Starfox and his fellow Titanians comes to light! Plus: The missing Avengers--found!
description.77: A defeated Captain America is subjected to torture and is forced to relive his worse memories over and again. Meanwhile, Sam, Bernie, and a catatonic Arnie devise a plan to escape from Mother Superior's trap. Its hard times for our heroes! Who will survive the Red Skull!
description.78: Time is running out! The imperial doomsday machine is about to cause armageddon-galaxy-wide! It's up to Luke and his band of con men to save the cosmos!
description.80: What’s ahead for Jim Rhodes as Iron Man? Find out here!
description.81: Ben volunteers to become the leader of an alien race's Air Force, so that they can combat a rival alien colony!
description.83: Bob Layton delivers another winner by combining simple, strong text with the immensely intense image of Hulk holding 150,000,000,000 tons of rock from crushing his fellow heroes.
description.86: The Answer has pushed Spider-Man to his absolute limit -- and forces him to make an impossible choice! Save the Black Cat, or defuse a deadly bomb?
description.87: Big surprise this issue! You've been clamoring for the return of this writer to the ranks of Marvel! And you've been clamoring for Daredevil to face this villain once again! Now it all happens in one thrill-packed tale! Think you can stand the suspense of waiting for this once-in-a-lifetime opus to come out?
description.88: Look, we have no idea how Tony Stark can ever return to a normal life, but he's come this far, so we think we'll stick around and see what happens! If only Iron Man himself could do so!
description.91: Mister Fantastic and She-Hulk rush to the aid of Wyatt Wingfoot's tribe. Back in New York, Sue bears the emotional weight of her miscarriage.
description.92: The mutant energy vampire Selene makes an attempt to capture Rachel Summers, a mutant from the future. The X-Men step in to save her!
description.94: Ant-Man: Scott Lang infiltrates the Time Variance Authority! Will the Fantastic Four ever wipe themselves clean from the TVA’s records? Mobius M. Mobius cannot let that be allowed.
description.96: Dazzler... a zombie? As actress and dancer Alison Blaire, Dazzler gets an undead transformation on the set of a music video.
description.99: Get ready! The Muppets come to Marvel!

0.text: The Human Torch against the menace of the Black Abbott and the Black Apostles! What they can do to your body and soul is unspeakable!

1.text: Kitty Pryde's father is in hot water with some Japanese businessmen. Things get worse when she stows away on a flight to Tokyo.

2.text: BERSERKER The death of an Avenger! The X-Men's greatest battle! And, introducing the all-new Spider-Woman!

3.text: The dreadful cold inside the Casket of Ancient Winters has been unleashed upon Midgard. Now, Odin unveils the history of Asgard that has been veiled in darkness. Discover the origin of the Odinpower and Surtur! Featuring Beta Ray Bill!

4.text: Will Namor, Puck and Marrina escape the ‘Master of the World'?

14.text: With Gargoyle under the control of a powerful mage, the Defenders are hesitant to fight their friend!

21.text: Baintronics, Inc. gets a hold of Hassle! Doctor Cyclobe makes his first appearance! Plus, introducing Iron Man of the year 2020!!

22.text: Who Is Captain Hero? That's what Luke and Danny have to find out! Because this erratic new super hero wants to join Heroes For Hire!

24.text: The Pack breaks into two groups in an attempted diversion to save their mummified parents!

25.text: Ben's feelings for Alicia become more confused when he shares a passionate kiss with Tarianna! Later, Ben falls victim to a village of other subterranean Thing-like creatures!

26.text: His name is The Black Abbot, and he can mesmerize people with his voice! Can Spidey and Nomad stop him, or the terrible Taskmaster from organizing street gangs in his behalf?

27.text: When smalltime crook Erik Josten gets a dose of Pym particles he becomes the mega man Goliath! Iron Man has his hands full and his repulsors charged, trying to wipe out Goliath before Goliath wipes out Los Angeles! The West Coast Avengers assemble in this giant-sized battle for the streets!

28.text: A LITTLE DEATH Galactus prepares to destroy both the heroes and the villians! Now, as both sides of the engagement plan their next move, two MIA soldiers make their return!

29.text: Malekith, the Accursed, has revered his long-lost treasure, the Casket of Ancient Winters! Now he prepares to unleash its deadly contents on an unsuspecting world from his realm beneath the Cotswolds of England!

30.text: Marrina emerges from Lake Ontario and ferociously attacks Puck! Snowbird reveals her true identity to her lover, Doug Thompson.

35.text: WHAT IF…LOKI HAD FOUND THE HAMMER OF THOR? Trickster God Loki is first to claim Mjolnir in this What If? tale. Will Thor's mischievous brother prove worthy of a Thunder God's power?

40.text: Dracula rises once more! While visiting Hannibal King in Boston, Strange learns that the ancient vampire and his Black Cult may be afoot and active.

41.text: Cloud undergoes a physical transformation and reveals a shocking secret concerning Moondragon. The Defenders must battle a ghost of Gargoyle!

43.text: When his brother and sisters are kidnapped by the Snarks, it's up to Jack to save them alone!

44.text: Featuring a look back into Aunt May's youth, as she is haunted today by an old love, and a secret from her past! How will her web-slinging nephew save her from the dangers without, and within? Plus: a solo tale of the Black Cat!

49.text: Cage and the Fist hobnob with the social elite when they take Jeryn Hogarth's beautiful daughter to her debutante's ball! But...amid the glamor and glitter we find Nightshade, Stiletto, Discus, Man Mountain Marko, and the Eel! You'll never guess what they're doing there...and it's no picnic for our heroes! Guest starring Wonder Man, the Beast, and the Wasp!

50.text: Final issue. For this farewell, you'll see Ka-Zar transported to another dimension--but what awaits the Jungle Lord in the Land of Cancelled Heroes--we cannot say!

51.text: Alpha Flight rides in to the rescue!

56.text: Machine Man is reassembled in the year 2020, a strange, wired world that portends a dangerous vision of the future! And he’s back with a vengeance!

57.text: Doctor Strange proves to be Bruce Banner’s final shot at salvation.

58.text: THE BATTLE OF THE FOUR ARMIES The villains have the upper hand! As they plan their final strike, Galactus' mysterious vigil comes to a surprising end...

59.text: When the time is right, a mortal may cross over into the enchanted Realm of Faerie...and be lost forever. That time is now. And there is but one man who can save the lost mortal...his name is Thor!

60.text: Alpha Flight members each pursue a solo career!

61.text: Ben and Tarianna are enjoying each other's company, when they are interrupted by Gruhl of Shalfbut!

64.text: Spider-Man and Iron Man team up against the menace of…Magma!

65.text: As Manslaughter is brought to justice, the Defenders run into trouble with a mutant arsonist that was hired to kill the entire team!

74.text: The Power Pack kids break into the lab where the matter/antimatter converter is scheduled to be tested! Will their lack of superhero experience prove fatal for the team?

79.text: The Reaper is going to avenge the murder of a policeman...even if he has to kill innocent people to do it!

81.text: Ben volunteers to become the leader of an alien race's Air Force, so that they can combat a rival alien colony!

82.text: Hulk takes on Doctor Strange’s nemesis, Nightmare!

83.text: SITUATION: HOPELESS The heroes' HQ has been destroyed! Thor has been captured by Enchantress and taken straight to the villains! Doctor Doom scores his first kill!
Bob Layton delivers another winner by combining simple, strong text with the immensely intense image of Hulk holding 150,000,000,000 tons of rock from crushing his fellow heroes.

84.text: The Hunting Horn of Faerie has been sounded and it can mean only one thing: someone hath called the Wild Hunt. And that someone is none other than Malekith! What can Thor do to stop this dread menace?

85.text: Heather struggles with the death of her husband during a series of disturbing dreams. Not letting it crush her spirit, she renews her commitment to Alpha Flight!

86.text: The Answer has pushed Spider-Man to his absolute limit -- and forces him to make an impossible choice! Save the Black Cat, or defuse a deadly bomb?

90.text: WHAT IF…SPIDER-MAN'S UNCLE BEN HAD LIVED? Spider-Man's origin as we know it is rewritten, when Aunt May is killed instead of Uncle Ben! And the ramifications are severe!

93.text: Spider-Man teams up with Moon Knight to bust a murderous criminal organization!

94.text: Doctor Strange helps the Priests of Bjarghan determine whether or not they are “The Chosen One.”

95.text: The Defenders are on edge because of multiple threats from Manslaughter. He goes after each member of the Defenders. Cloud and Moondragon’s relationship evolves.

97.text: The Plunderer has just discovered a new supply of anti-metal! And unless Ka-Zar and Shanna can stop him from selling it to the highest bidder, world-wide chaos will result!

98.text: When Luke and Danny delve into the mysterious past of a rock singer, they may not find what they're looking for...
